    "created_at": "2015-03-31T15:44:29Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-05-12T10:05:18Z",
    "closed_at": "2015-05-12T10:05:18Z",
    "body": "Currently there is a lot of inline javascript. In order to support [CSP](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Security/CSP/CSP_policy_directives) (and mitigate XSS) the content should be split by type. Html content should only contain html and JavaScript should be put in .js files and not be mixed within the html.\r\n\r\nWould you guys consider a pull request where I have moved all inline javascript into separate .js files?\r\n\r\nSo i.e. layout/_scripts/fancy-box.swig would be changed from:\r\n\r\n    {% if theme.fancybox %}\r\n      <script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"{{ url_for(theme.vendors) }}/fancybox/source/jquery.fancybox.pack.js\"></script>\r\n      <script type=\"text/javascript\">\r\n        $(document).ready(function() {\r\n          $(\".fancybox\").fancybox();\r\n        });\r\n      </script>\r\n    {% endif %}\r\n\r\nto something like:\r\n\r\n    {% if theme.fancybox %}\r\n      <script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"{{ url_for(theme.vendors) }}/fancybox/source/jquery.fancybox.pack.js\"></script>\r\n      <script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"{{ url_for(theme.vendors) }}/fancybox_loader.js\"></script>\r\n    {% endif %}\r\n\r\nand source/vendors/fancybox_loader.js would contain:\r\n\r\n        $(document).ready(function() {\r\n          $(\".fancybox\").fancybox();\r\n        });\r\n\r\nThis would enable the browser to enforce stronger and simpler rules on what to parse and prevents some commonly used XSS techniques. Using CSP and separation of concerns is generally a good thing imho."
